Movie: The Killing of a Sacred Deer

Review: i used to be a scott pilgrim's enthusiastic in the 2010s and wanted to love this version so much, but the pacing was way too off for me. at times, it felt like it would never end, and tbh it took me more than a month to finish it. but i do appreciate the idea and the original casting coming back for this project. i'd say some of the plots here were fun, but oh boy i guess the physicality and the creative visual choices of a live action were missing most of the time to make it work for me at this pacing.
every decision pta made here was on point.
nooo sydney sweeney please don't cry alone at the opera house you're so sexy
